pageContext.claim: “We had a you know, that people would call it, it's 306 to 223. That's a lot. Remember, they said I couldn't get to 270 and they were right. I got to 306.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump actually won 304 to 232. He was off on his total because two faithless electors refused to give him their votes in the Electoral College. Hillary Clinton won nine more votes than Trump claimed.
